cs.IR, cs.GT, cs.DS, cs.LG, cs.AI. 

The paper deals with optimization problems in the context of internet search and advertising, which suggests that it could belong to several sub-categories. However, given the focus on search-based advertising auctions and the modeling of the entire process, cs.IR (Information Retrieval) seems to be the most likely category. The paper also mentions game-theoretic aspects, which could place it in cs.GT (Game Theory), and the optimization problems suggest cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the use of randomized strategies and inapproximability results suggest cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
